1
00:00:00,584 --> 00:00:02,294
♪

2
00:00:02,294 --> 00:00:03,378
Aniplex.

3
00:00:14,765 --> 00:00:31,365
♪

4
00:00:31,365 --> 00:00:32,574
(gunshot)

5
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:35,077
(singing in Japanese)

6
00:00:40,332 --> 00:00:46,672
♪

7
00:02:05,417 --> 00:02:07,878
(growling)

8
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:09,921
(grunting)

9
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:21,600
♪

10
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,769
Did you hate me?

11
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:27,981
Did you hate me so much
that you became this?

12
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:30,359
(yelling)

13
00:02:30,359 --> 00:02:39,910
♪

14
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:41,787
Origin rounds.

15
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:44,748
They cause the target's
mana to go out of control,

16
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,958
causing their body
to rip itself apart.

17
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:50,962
What?

18
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:53,131
Time alter.

19
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:54,383
Double accel!

20
00:02:54,383 --> 00:03:09,314
♪

21
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:12,025
The origin rounds are working.

22
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:15,153
No, I understand.

23
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:18,407
He's using command
seals as his mana source.

24
00:03:18,407 --> 00:03:21,159
By the time the round
strikes and takes effect,

25
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:23,704
the command seal mana
source has already vanished.

26
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:28,708
Since he doesn't use his own
magic circuits for attacks,

27
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:31,795
the origin rounds'
magic won't work.

28
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,880
But if I can land a solid hit,

29
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,508
it'll still be strong
enough to kill him.

30
00:03:36,508 --> 00:03:38,343
♪

31
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,179
Don't think you'll
escape next time.

32
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:43,765
Now that I know you're
moving at double speed,

33
00:03:43,765 --> 00:03:47,185
I simply need to adjust the
distance to compensate for it.

34
00:03:47,185 --> 00:04:00,615
♪

35
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:01,867
He's fast!

36
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:10,375
♪

37
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,586
(choking)

38
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:15,380
♪

39
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,382
(yelling)

40
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:19,801
♪

41
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:22,721
The depth of your
violent madness...

42
00:04:22,721 --> 00:04:25,182
(yelling)

43
00:04:26,475 --> 00:04:28,268
...is that my fault as well?

44
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:45,619
♪

45
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,078
Is it?

46
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:48,747
(clanking)

47
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:50,207
Is it my fault?

48
00:04:50,207 --> 00:05:00,717
♪

49
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:03,720
(gun firing)

50
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:07,933
♪

51
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:11,186
Time alter, double accel.

52
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:30,205
♪

53
00:05:30,205 --> 00:05:31,957
(gun firing)

54
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:35,377
♪

55
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:38,171
(gasping)

56
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:46,638
♪

57
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:48,765
(panting)

58
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:59,860
♪

59
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:03,113
I'm at a massive
disadvantage at close range.

60
00:06:03,113 --> 00:06:04,990
I've lost my Calico.

61
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:06,950
My Contender needs reloading.

62
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:10,662
However, Avalon.

63
00:06:10,662 --> 00:06:15,208
♪

64
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,252
He has healing ability
that allows him

65
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:20,171
to instantly regenerate
a demolished heart?

66
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:23,383
Well then, I'll have
to destroy the brain.

67
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:26,887
But I can't use my right arm.

68
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:30,181
Avalon will even work
on self‐inflicted wounds.

69
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:33,560
I have a knife I can use
and two grenades left.

70
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:38,732
I have 12 blades remaining
and eight spare command seals.

71
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,775
Time alter.

72
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,235
Triple accel.

73
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:53,455
♪

74
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:55,582
(bubbling)

75
00:06:55,582 --> 00:07:21,816
♪

76
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:23,151
Time alter.

77
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:25,945
Square accel!

78
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:57,310
♪

79
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,479
(exploding)

80
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:12,075
(clanking)

81
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:21,084
But, even so, I
will win the Grail.

82
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:25,422
If I do not, there
will be nothing I can do

83
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:27,465
to atone to you.

84
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:35,974
Even after all
that has happened

85
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:38,643
you would still
take up your sword

86
00:08:38,643 --> 00:08:40,729
for a reason such as that?

87
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,900
What a difficult person you are.

88
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:48,903
(clattering)

89
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,376
(rain pouring)

90
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:08,882
Where am I?

91
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,848
I knew you would
come, Kiritsugu.

92
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:22,729
I had faith that you would be
the one to reach this place.

93
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,274
‐Iri.
‐This is where the wish

94
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:28,985
you have lived
for will be granted.

95
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:32,447
We are inside the Grail
that you have been seeking.

96
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:39,370
That is the Holy Grail.

97
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:41,206
It has yet to take form,

98
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:44,375
but the vessel itself
is more than filled.

99
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:47,420
All you need do now
is offer it your prayer.

100
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:52,425
Only then will it be able to
go out into the physical world.

101
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:57,889
Now, please, hurry and
give the Grail its form!

102
00:09:57,889 --> 00:10:01,392
Kiritsugu, you have proven
yourself more than worthy

103
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:03,686
to define its existence.

104
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:07,690
Who are you, really?

105
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:09,984
I am Irisviel, as you see.

106
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,444
No.

107
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,114
If the Grail is prepared
to receive a wish,

108
00:10:14,114 --> 00:10:15,865
then she is already...

109
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,369
Answer me!

110
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:20,870
It's true.

111
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:23,832
I will not deny that this
is no more than a mask.

112
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:26,918
You see, unless I use

113
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:29,879
a preexisting
personality as a shell,

114
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:32,048
I cannot communicate
with others.

115
00:10:32,048 --> 00:10:35,844
However, the personality
of Irisviel that I recorded

116
00:10:35,844 --> 00:10:38,471
is undeniably the real thing.

117
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:40,473
And so I have
inherited the last wish

118
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:43,309
that Irisviel
held in her heart.

119
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,104
Are you the will
of the Holy Grail?

120
00:10:46,104 --> 00:10:50,150
I am, that interpretation
is not incorrect.

121
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:53,611
I have my own will
and my own wish.

122
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:56,614
I have the will to be
born into the world.

123
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,199
No way.

124
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:01,035
If that's the case,
then how does the Grail

125
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:03,705
intend to totally
fulfill my wish?

126
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:07,792
Well, Kiritsugu,
that is something

127
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:09,836
that you should know far better

128
00:11:09,836 --> 00:11:12,130
than anyone else
could possibly know.

129
00:11:12,130 --> 00:11:13,840
What?

130
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,634
You learned exactly
how to save the world

131
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:19,012
a long, long time ago.

132
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:22,473
So I will do exactly
as you always did‐‐

133
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:27,312
to carry out your will and to
ultimately answer your prayer.

134
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:29,522
What are you talking about?

135
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:32,984
I have no choice.

136
00:11:32,984 --> 00:11:35,737
The only way is to
have you go and explore

137
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:38,448
that same question
through your inner self.

138
00:11:40,158 --> 00:11:40,909
(gasps)

139
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:45,622
This is...

140
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:51,336
Three hundred are on one ship,

141
00:11:51,336 --> 00:11:53,838
200 on another.

142
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,840
‐What the‐‐
‐Five hundred total

143
00:11:55,840 --> 00:12:00,303
passengers and crew,
plus Kiritsugu Emiya.

144
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:02,972
Let's assume that
these 501 people

145
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:06,017
are humanity's
last survivors.

146
00:12:06,017 --> 00:12:09,062
Giant holes simultaneously
open up in both ships,

147
00:12:09,062 --> 00:12:10,521
crippling them.

148
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:14,734
Kiritsugu alone has the
skills needed to repair a ship.

149
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:19,113
Now then, which one of the
ships would you choose to fix?

150
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:23,034
Simple‐‐the one
holding 300 people.

151
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:25,536
As soon as you
make that decision,

152
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:28,289
the 200 passengers
on the other ship

153
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:31,042
kidnap you and
take you prisoner.

154
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:33,920
They demand that you
fix their ship first.

155
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:36,881
What will you do?

156
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,925
I would...

157
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:41,094
(gun firing)

158
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:05,493
♪

159
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:08,121
You would kill
all 200 passengers.

160
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:12,041
That is correct, that is
the Kiritsugu Emiya we know.

161
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:14,585
(cell phone ringing)

162
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:18,589
Next, the surviving
300 passengers

163
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,591
abandon their damaged craft.

164
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:22,969
They split themselves
between two new ships

165
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:24,762
and continue their journey.

166
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:27,724
This time, there are 200 on one,

167
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:30,268
and 100 on the other.

168
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:33,730
But again, holes open
the hulls of both ships

169
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:36,232
at exactly the same time.

170
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,942
Wait.

171
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:40,862
The hundred in the smaller
ship take you prisoner,

172
00:13:40,862 --> 00:13:44,949
and like the others, demand
that you fix their ship first.

173
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:46,951
Now what will you do?

174
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:49,454
You already know, but you...

175
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:51,497
(beeping)

176
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:55,877
♪

177
00:13:55,877 --> 00:13:57,837
(explosion)

178
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:05,803
♪

179
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:08,139
Yes, you made
the right decision.

180
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:10,349
No, that's impossible!

181
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:12,185
How can that be
the right decision?

182
00:14:12,185 --> 00:14:17,023
Two hundred survived, but
300 died so they could live.

183
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:18,733
The scales are
tipped the wrong way!

184
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:22,111
No, your calculations
were correct.

185
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:26,741
You made a choice to sacrifice
the few to save the many.

186
00:14:26,741 --> 00:14:29,994
Isn't that right,
Kiritsugu Emiya?

187
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:32,038
You have consistently
chosen to kill those

188
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:34,665
in the lighter
side of the scales,

189
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:37,376
even if it meant leaving
a long trail of bodies

190
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:39,128
behind you in your wake.

191
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:41,964
If it saved lives,
the lives of the saved

192
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:44,926
must've been worth more
than those you destroyed.

193
00:14:44,926 --> 00:14:48,096
♪

194
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:51,474
This‐‐this is what
you wanted to show me?

195
00:14:51,474 --> 00:14:54,352
Yes, this is your truth.

196
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:57,271
The answer that lies
within Kiritsugu Emiya.

197
00:14:57,271 --> 00:15:00,149
The course of action that
should be taken by the Grail

198
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:02,193
as an all‐powerful wish‐granter.

199
00:15:02,193 --> 00:15:03,194
No.

200
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:05,363
No, this is not what I want!

201
00:15:05,363 --> 00:15:08,741
I want there to be another
way to save the world.

202
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,077
That's why I believed

203
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:13,663
that a miracle
was my only hope.

204
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:15,540
Your wish cannot include

205
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:19,252
a method you yourself
don't already know.

206
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:21,963
If your wish is
the save the world,

207
00:15:21,963 --> 00:15:25,675
it must be done in a manner
that you can fully comprehend.

208
00:15:25,675 --> 00:15:27,468
Like hell!

209
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:30,721
How in the hell can
you call that a miracle?

210
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:34,142
But it is.

211
00:15:34,142 --> 00:15:37,228
The deed you tried
so hard to accomplish

212
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:39,313
and failed to do on your own

213
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:43,484
can be accomplished on a scale
beyond the power of any man.

214
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:46,696
If that is not a
miracle, what is?

215
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:50,491
♪

216
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:53,411
Father.

217
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:54,579
(gunshot)

218
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:01,752
♪

219
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:02,879
Natalia.

220
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:06,507
♪

221
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:08,134
Kiritsugu Emiya.

222
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:11,220
You truly are Angra Mainyu‐‐

223
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:15,641
the one worthy to bear
all the evil in the world.

224
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:18,644
Now, the final question.

225
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,272
♪

226
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:23,191
Three remain.

227
00:16:23,191 --> 00:16:26,652
♪

228
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:30,323
Will you save two or choose one?

229
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:37,538
♪

230
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:44,128
Welcome home, Daddy!

231
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:48,466
Oh, I'm so happy that
you're finally back!

232
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:53,137
You understand now, right?

233
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:55,431
This is all the Holy Grail

234
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:57,600
granting your
heart's fervent prayer.

235
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:00,645
♪

236
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:04,232
All you need do now
is to wish for it,

237
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:08,527
to bring back your wife,
to take back your daughter.

238
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:16,202
♪

239
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:18,496
I won't be able
to go looking

240
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:21,207
for chestnuts
with you anymore.

241
00:17:21,207 --> 00:17:23,626
It's okay, don't
worry about it!

242
00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:24,961
I'll be happy just as long

243
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:27,713
as you and Mother are
with me from now on.

244
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:29,382
Thank you.

245
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:33,010
Daddy loves you,
my precious Ilya.

246
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:36,931
If nothing else,
I swear that's true.

247
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:39,684
(giggles)

248
00:17:39,684 --> 00:17:41,644
(clicking)

249
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:46,732
Goodbye, Ilya.

250
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,318
Ilya!

251
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,319
Ilya!

252
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,488
Ilya, Ilya!

253
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:53,739
Ilya!

254
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:54,824
Ilya.

255
00:17:54,824 --> 00:17:56,367
(clicking)

256
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:57,785
But why?

257
00:17:57,785 --> 00:18:00,121
Why would you do this?

258
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:02,164
My love, you killed our Ilya!

259
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:04,834
♪

260
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:06,961
(choking)

261
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:08,921
♪

262
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:12,049
My love...

263
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:14,510
why?

264
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:19,557
Why do you...refuse us...

265
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:21,392
and the Grail?

266
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:23,811
(gasping)

267
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:27,481
Six billion people on the Earth.

268
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:28,983
I...

269
00:18:28,983 --> 00:18:31,235
curse you...

270
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:34,071
Kiritsugu Emiya.

271
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:36,032
Versus you two.

272
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:39,869
Angra Mainyu curses you.

273
00:18:39,869 --> 00:18:42,038
That's why.

274
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:44,081
‐You'll suffer...
‐That's why...

275
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:48,127
‐...till the day you die.
‐... I have to kill you.

276
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:51,672
‐I will...
‐And I will save...

277
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:54,258
‐the world.
‐Never forget‐‐

278
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:56,302
(snapping)

279
00:18:56,302 --> 00:19:01,766
♪

280
00:19:13,361 --> 00:19:15,905
(clicking)

281
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:17,865
(sloshing)

282
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:26,540
What a boring
conclusion to this fight.

283
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,336
Why did you refuse it?

284
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:32,630
You were able
to see all that?

285
00:19:32,630 --> 00:19:34,965
I thought you sacrificed
everything you had

286
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:36,550
including your family

287
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,095
in order to make
it to this point.

288
00:19:39,095 --> 00:19:40,805
How can you simply
deny the worth

289
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:44,100
of something you
worked so hard to attain?

290
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:47,728
It's so foolish, I
cannot understand it.

291
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:50,356
The tremendous toll it demands

292
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:53,526
is far greater than
anything it can offer.

293
00:19:53,526 --> 00:19:55,361
That's the simple truth.

294
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:59,281
That thing is no
omnipotent wish‐granter.

295
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:00,908
Then give the damn thing to me!

296
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:01,826
(cocks gun)

297
00:20:01,826 --> 00:20:03,828
You may not think you need it,

298
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:06,163
but I most certainly do.

299
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:10,126
If it‐‐if it is given
the life it is seeking,

300
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:12,586
then it can surely
answer my every doubt

301
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:15,297
and finally bring
everything into clarity.

302
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,633
The Grail longs for
a life of its own,

303
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,760
longs for its own birth!

304
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:23,222
Please, don't kill it, it's‐‐

305
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:24,640
(gunshot)

306
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:33,524
No, you are the fool
I can't understand.

307
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:36,944
(door opens)

308
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:43,534
♪

309
00:20:43,534 --> 00:20:45,786
Oh, Iris, you...

310
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:48,122
♪

311
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:49,832
You're late, Saber!

312
00:20:49,832 --> 00:20:51,834
I realized you were
enjoying yourself

313
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:53,377
with your old Mad Dog,

314
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:55,296
but it is imprudent
to the extreme

315
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:57,673
to keep me waiting like you did.

316
00:20:57,673 --> 00:21:00,134
Archer.

317
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:02,720
Look at that
delightful expression,

318
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:05,514
like that of a
ravenous wild dog.

319
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:09,185
Get out of my way.

320
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:10,853
You haven't won.

321
00:21:10,853 --> 00:21:13,981
The Holy Grail belongs to me!

322
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,567
(grunting)

323
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,779
Dear Saber, it is
when you are delusional

324
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,822
and crawling in the dirt

325
00:21:21,822 --> 00:21:24,825
that you are at
your most beautiful.

326
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:28,746
Lay down your
blade and be my wife.

327
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:32,917
A Grail that grants miracles?

328
00:21:32,917 --> 00:21:35,252
Where is the sense
in totally obsessing

329
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:36,879
over something so dubious?

330
00:21:38,589 --> 00:21:42,468
Abandon these foolish ideals
and childish vows of yours.

331
00:21:42,468 --> 00:21:46,639
From now on, seek only me and
devote yourself to me alone.

332
00:21:46,639 --> 00:21:50,518
If you do, I swear as
King of All Creation

333
00:21:50,518 --> 00:21:54,605
that I shall give you every
pleasure the world has to offer.

334
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:59,610
You would steal the
Holy Grail from me

335
00:21:59,610 --> 00:22:02,279
for such utter nonsense?

336
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:03,447
(grunting)

337
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:08,369
I was not asking
for your opinion.

338
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:10,412
I am informing
you of my decision.

339
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:15,334
Now, let us hear your response.

340
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:16,544
I refuse.

341
00:22:16,544 --> 00:22:18,796
I would never‐‐

342
00:22:18,796 --> 00:22:22,216
Shyness has left you at
a loss for words, I see.

343
00:22:22,216 --> 00:22:23,509
That's fine.

344
00:22:23,509 --> 00:22:26,637
You may answer wrongly
as many times as you like.

345
00:22:26,637 --> 00:22:29,014
If you would learn
the joy of serving me,

346
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:32,893
you must first learn the
exquisite pain of it as well.

347
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:40,734
♪

348
00:22:40,734 --> 00:22:42,403
Kiritsugu!

349
00:22:42,403 --> 00:22:46,115
♪

350
00:22:46,115 --> 00:22:50,035
Ah, then you have
finally made your decision.

351
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:52,663
In the name of Kiritsugu Emiya,

352
00:22:52,663 --> 00:22:54,665
and by my command seal...

353
00:22:54,665 --> 00:22:57,418
Give me the Holy Grail.

354
00:22:57,418 --> 00:23:01,547
...I order you, use
your Noble Phantasm.

355
00:23:01,547 --> 00:23:03,382
Destroy the Grail.

356
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:07,011
♪

357
00:23:07,011 --> 00:23:10,723
Impossible‐‐what
are you doing, Saber!

358
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:12,224
No!

359
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:14,184
By my third command seal,

360
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:15,436
I order you again.

361
00:23:16,937 --> 00:23:20,941
But why, Kiritsugu‐‐
you of all people?

362
00:23:20,941 --> 00:23:23,319
‐Why this?
‐Damn you to Hell.

363
00:23:23,319 --> 00:23:25,779
You dare interrupt my nuptials?

364
00:23:25,779 --> 00:23:29,241
‐Mongrel!
‐Saber, destroy...

365
00:23:30,409 --> 00:23:32,202
Stop!

366
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:33,787
...the Holy Grail.

367
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:11,468
I remember the look on his face,

368
00:25:11,468 --> 00:25:13,429
the tears in his eyes‐‐

369
00:25:13,429 --> 00:25:18,267
a man filled with joy
from the bottom of his heart.

370
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:20,686
I felt jealous of him.

371
00:25:20,686 --> 00:25:23,105
He said, "Thank you."

